 tanks, either warriors and knights who will have more hit points making for more efficient cheals and more reliable taunt, or a monk who has less hp and no insta taunt but makes the mobs die faster and has an avoidance to more or less make up for the hp difference. <br>
As for the get out of death free card we have, well, sks and necros get it too and even wth that ability I still have my fair share of deaths, after all, fd can fail. I think you will also find that on high end raids, monks have one of the highest fatality rates since they do the pulling of those nasty mobs. Dont get me wrong, fd is an amazing tool, but it hardly keeps us from ever dying. <br>
I honestly dont see what the problem is, monks have always BEEN tanks, and unless Verant nerfs us to high heaven we will always be tanks. Actually, strike that, I DO know what the problem is. Up until NToV and high end Luclin, monks always had the substantially lower hp than warriors and now that we can top over 6k buffed those top 3% of monks are making the other tanks nervous. Go ahead, BE afraid of those very few monks capable of reaching that mark. Just remember, the other 97% of all monks in the game will never be that good and although we can tank in xp groups just fine, we wont be taking mt spots in raids. <br>
