<br>
Monk has gone such a drastic change that it's not even funny. You went from crappy ac and crappy hp and NO weapons to ... great ac (Velious), great hp items (velious + luclin), and obscene weapons (kunark + velious + luclin). The REASON you had such crappy items/ac/hps because your skill levels were OBSCENELY high (230-240 caps for weapons and defense skills compared to a warriors crappy 200.) and you had alot of token abilities (fd, mend.)<br>
<br>
Kunark attempted to balance it by raising alot of warrior skills into the 250 range, and to compensate monks for that, you got absurd ratio weapons (yeah, the class that was supposed to be have the least need for equipment gets the best equipment god what retards). Warriors still had a strong AC advantage, and a noticeable HP advantage, as well as triple attack (to give them a dps edge.)<br>
<br>
Velious raised everyones AC and everyone's damage output. However, high end kunark warriors were already capped on AC. Monks gained triple attack, began to close the hp gap with high end velious hp items, closed in on the softcap for AC, got their own superior damage table. However, since mod rod 2 wasn't around yet, neither was alot of FT, defensive was crucial. Yes, defensive is a CRUTCH to people with 7k+ hp now, but lemme tell you, you wouldn't have gotten to 7k+hp without defensive in the first place.<br>
<br>
Luclin really screwed it all up by putting alot of AA that should have been warrior only, into archetype abilities which alot of people share. On top of that, warriors got NO class AA that made them better at what the are supposed to do. In addition, lots more EASY to get hp items, ND3... the warrior 400 hp bonus meant alot when everyone only had like 1000-3000hp... it means jack sh!t when everyone has 2000-6000hp. Even MORE ludicrous easy to get AC items... the warrior advantages just don't mean much anymore.<br>
